1
00:00:00,170 --> 00:00:06,950
In this video, we are going to run Docker Compose on Visual Studio in order to set up PostgreSQL database

2
00:00:06,950 --> 00:00:08,210
on the environment.

3
00:00:08,930 --> 00:00:15,350
So first of all, please open the Visual Studio and also open the Docker desktop and make sure that

4
00:00:15,350 --> 00:00:17,090
your Docker desktop is running.

5
00:00:17,090 --> 00:00:23,270
And after that you can come to Visual Studio and right click the Docker Compose as a startup project.

6
00:00:24,040 --> 00:00:27,490
And run the Docker compose profile from the Visual Studio.

7
00:00:28,150 --> 00:00:33,580
This action will bring up our PostgreSQL database as defined in the Docker compose files.

8
00:00:35,590 --> 00:00:37,720
Okay if you open the.

9
00:00:38,410 --> 00:00:39,580
Docker desktop.

10
00:00:39,580 --> 00:00:45,160
You can see that this time we have two PostgreSQL database on Docker desktop.

11
00:00:45,160 --> 00:00:51,400
So after running the Docker compose, we have verified that we have two PostgreSQL instance running

12
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:53,410
one for the catalog db.

13
00:00:53,410 --> 00:00:59,920
And if you look at the catalog db port numbers, you can see that this is exposing the default port

14
00:00:59,920 --> 00:01:02,920
number and another for the basket db.

15
00:01:02,920 --> 00:01:10,690
Exposing the PostgreSQL database 5433 that we have exposed to our local computer, and the internal

16
00:01:10,690 --> 00:01:12,220
port numbers are the same.

17
00:01:12,220 --> 00:01:14,140
These are the five, four, three, two.

18
00:01:14,170 --> 00:01:19,390
These are the internal port numbers, that is the actual PostgreSQL default port number.

19
00:01:19,630 --> 00:01:25,840
So now we have successfully run two database into our computer and docker compose environment.

20
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:32,080
Now it is time to browse the databases and see the database and tables into the basket database.

21
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:38,800
I recommended to using Pgadmin for more user friendly interface and managing our databases for that

22
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:41,140
purpose, please open the Pgadmin.

23
00:01:41,140 --> 00:01:44,770
You can download Pgadmin from their official website.

24
00:01:44,860 --> 00:01:49,780
After opening the PGA admin, you can register servers for Catalog and basket DB.

25
00:01:49,810 --> 00:01:56,020
You can come here and right click and register a new server and give the server name as a local server

26
00:01:56,020 --> 00:01:58,000
name as a catalog or basket DB.

27
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:04,330
For example, you can give basket db and after that in the connection tab, you can give the server

28
00:02:04,330 --> 00:02:11,290
name as a localhost, and this time basket db will be hosting as a five, four, three and three in

29
00:02:11,290 --> 00:02:14,080
order to access basket db in different port.

30
00:02:14,080 --> 00:02:16,780
So you can create this kind of server registration.

31
00:02:16,780 --> 00:02:22,210
And after that you can come here and listing your servers for catalog and basket DB.

32
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:24,670
Here you can see that I have created basket DB.

33
00:02:24,670 --> 00:02:28,960
And you can see the empty doc products table is created successfully.

34
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:35,290
And if you open the basket DB you can see that basket DB also connected in different port from our local

35
00:02:35,290 --> 00:02:35,980
computer.

36
00:02:35,980 --> 00:02:40,420
And if you go to the tables, we can right click and refresh this page.

37
00:02:40,420 --> 00:02:45,970
There is no table is created yet because we are looking for the basket DB database now.

38
00:02:45,970 --> 00:02:50,680
And we didn't start our basket DB application or we didn't send any request.

39
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:53,980
That's why Martin is only create database for us.

40
00:02:53,980 --> 00:03:00,940
So as you can see that we have connected two different database into our local computer and we are ready

41
00:03:00,940 --> 00:03:07,090
